msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Second volume of a 10th-century dictionary of the Arabic language. Words are indexed by their last root letter, with this volume covering the letters zāʼ to lām. Marginal notes by a reader and proofreader. Later pastedown on inner cover has remedies written in Arabic and Persian.

supportDesc.extent: 203 leaves : 269 x 172 (198 x 125) mm. bound to 269 x 180 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated title page (f. 1r); rubrications in red, including headings, guide words and finding aids in the margins.

binding.p: Repaired black leather, blind-stamped central mandorla with two pendants on the vertical axis and cornerpieces.

origin.p: Item is undated, possibly copied in Egypt or Syria in the 14th century.

history.provenance: Several effaced ownership stamps on title page (f. 1r) and last page verso (f. 203v).
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Nov. 2000.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
